alexatesting

Class TestDataTellResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • alexatesting.TestDataTellResponse

  • public class TestDataTellResponse
extends Object
    For JUnit testing, create JSON responses that we expect will match to the actual JSON output from our application.

    The Alexa service exchanges JSON data with our application that conforms to the structure in "JSON Interface Reference for Custom Skills." For JUnit testing, we create conforming JSON requests, send them through the application's stream handler (TrashDaySpeechletRequestStreamHandler), and read the JSON response output. Tests are successful if the actual application JSON output matches an expected JSON response.

    This class creates JSON responses that we expect will match to the actual JSON output from our application.

    Author:
    J. Todd Baldwin
    See Also:
    Alexa Skills Kit Docs: JSON Interface Reference for Custom Skills
